# nety Frontend Build — Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Rebuild `apps/nety.html` as a bold "Kinetic Mesh" landing that doubles as the flove access point (registration, invite web, MyNet/permissions, four-facet Verify, stars/stages), and polish the linked pages (profily, sety, new wizy) — all CSS-pure except one inline registration/stars script.

**Architecture:** A single self-contained `nety.html` extended section-by-section, reusing its existing dark Kinetic-Mesh design tokens (Fredoka + Space Mono, `--accent`/`--signal`). All new interactivity is CSS `:has()`/checkbox-driven *except* one small inline script for the registration form + stars/stage progress state. Everything is an interactive **mock** (no backend); the real flovenet/oasis backend is a separate future plan.

**Tech Stack:** Hand-written HTML/CSS/SVG, one vanilla-JS inline `<script>`, Google Fonts (Fredoka, Space Mono). No build step, no dependencies. Verification by rasterizing states to PNG (`convert`/`rsvg`) and reading them.

## Global Constraints

- **Source of truth:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-18-nety-access-ecosystem-design.md` (this plan implements its §8 page order and §3–§5 sections). Backend realization lives in `…-vs-flovenet-oasis-comparison.md` and is **out of scope here**.
- **CSS-pure everywhere on `nety.html` EXCEPT one inline `<script>`** covering: registration live outputs + stars/stage progress (accrue → cross stages → reveal passwords/open sections; never deducted). No other JS on nety.
- **Fonts:** Fredoka (display) + Space Mono (body) only. No Inter/Roboto/Arial. No new color hues on nety beyond existing tokens (`--accent:#8d89ff`, `--signal:#00f7a7`, dark field).
- **Each linked app keeps its own identity:** profily warm/light (orange `#ff9b5e`, Inter+Fraunces); sety dark-purple; wizy athenea (navy `#0d1430` + gold `#d4af37`).
- **Accessibility:** full `prefers-reduced-motion` static fallback; visible focus states; `.vh` visually-hidden inputs keep working.
- **Honesty:** one candid line near Access/Verify marking previews vs live (spec §6).
- **Workflow:** after each task, render-verify the changed state to PNG and Read it before committing (flove "render to verify" standard). At the end, commit + push to Gitea `localhost:3000/marc/flove` (main), message = prompt + explanation.
- **All data is mock/illustrative.** Trust weights, CU thresholds, stages are the provisional numbers from spec §4.2/§5.1.
- **Naming & tier model (spec §2.1) — use verbatim:** two tiered domains — **`nety` = hardware** (resource quota ladder) and **`appy` = data-software** (feature ladder), each `mini → basic → normal → advanced → super`. Stages are **`newbie · known · homie · expert · legend`** (NOT Joined/Contributor/Steward/Patron/Pillar). A **stage = an earned ceiling**; the **tier/mode you browse is your choice** (optionally activatable — a legend can browse mini). **Access gating:** `mini`(`nety`) is **open** (free client + contribute + `profily-mini`, no invite); `basic`(`appy`) is **invite-gated** (register to play & store apps; invites ~3/month, vertical web-of-trust). Profile names: **`profily-mini`** (open) ↔ **`profily`** (full). Advancement is substitutable: share nety hardware **or** give more authentication/trust.

