## File Structure

- `apps/nety.html` — **modify** (the whole build; one file, extended section by section).
- `apps/wizy.html` — **create** (new athenea finetuner-agents app).
- `apps/puzzy/sety.html` — **modify** (back-link, athen-ia Wizard, slider/glyph polish).
- `apps/profily.html` — **modify** (extended-profile framing, back-link, identity card, Trusts, MyNet/circles, MyWizy entry).
- No test files: verification is visual rasterization + structural greps (zero-JS check, link resolution).

Verification helper used throughout:
```bash
# rasterize a saved HTML/SVG state to PNG for visual review
cd /home/kdeneon/Documents/flove/apps
# (use the project's existing convert/rsvg toolchain; fall back to chromium --screenshot if needed)
```

---

## Task overview (build order — bottom-up)

**`nety.html` (Tasks 1–7), then linked apps (8–10), then wiring (11):**

1. **Kinetic Mesh shell** — background mesh, giant hero, re-skin existing content (CSS-pure).
2. **The one inline script** — `window.nety` registration + stars/stage state.
3. **Access** — passport (`profily-mini`), invite-gated registration (`mini→basic`), share-earn, invites, recovery mock.
4. **Public invite web** — CSS-pure SVG lineage tree + vouch threads + presence glows.
5. **MyNet & permissions** — f2f panel + coarse private-first pickers; MyWizy reference.
6. **Verify** — concentric scope rings (Personal/Local/Social/Global), identity ladder, publish gate.
7. **Stars, stages & tier model** — progress board, the two tier ladders, protected-section unlocks, honesty line, final page order.
8. **`wizy.html`** — new athenea finetuner-agents app.
9. **`sety.html`** — back-link, athen-ia Wizard + wizy link, slider/glyph polish.
10. **`profily.html`** — extended-profile framing, identity card, Trusts, MyNet/circles, MyWizy entry.
11. **Cross-link pass + Gitea push** — resolve all links, invariant checks, commit/push to main.

> Each task ends with a render-verify (chromium/convert → PNG → Read) before its commit.
> The flovenet/oasis backend is a **separate future plan** (see end), not built here.

---

### Task 1: Kinetic Mesh shell (background, hero, re-skinned existing content)

Rebuild the existing nety content (hero, 3 demos, stack, phase board, candid note) under the bold Kinetic-Mesh language. No new sections yet — this task proves the aesthetic.

**Files:**
- Modify: `apps/nety.html` (whole file — keep existing content, restyle; widen `.wrap` ~1100px)

**Interfaces:**
- Produces: design tokens + classes later tasks reuse — `.passport`, `.glass` (translucent glass card), `.mesh-bg` (fixed background layer), `.sec` (section heading), the orbit-mark SVG, `--accent`/`--signal`/glow shadows. Later tasks add sections inside `.wrap` using these.

- [ ] **Step 1: Add the mesh background + grain layer**
  Add a fixed full-bleed `.mesh-bg` div: intensified radial gradient-mesh (existing purple/green), 2–3 pure-SVG orbiting node groups at varied radii/speeds (extend existing `.orbit` spin keyframes), faint drifting link-lines, a CSS data-URI grain overlay. `position:fixed; inset:0; pointer-events:none; z-index:0`. Content wrapper gets `position:relative; z-index:1`.

- [ ] **Step 2: Enlarge the hero**
  Wordmark `NETY` → `font-size:clamp(4.5rem,20vw,11rem)`; orbit-mark scaled up and overlapping; lead on a diagonal axis; CTAs as glowing pills. Add the staggered page-load reveal (`animation-delay`: wordmark→lead→cards→mesh).

- [ ] **Step 3: Re-skin existing sections to glass node-cards**
  The 3 "What nety is" demo cards → `.glass` (translucent, `backdrop-filter:blur`, glowing border intensifying on hover/expand), connected by faint link-lines. Keep their existing `:has()` expand demos verbatim — only restyle. Stack chips → glowing tokens; phase board pills → luminous; keep the candid note.

- [ ] **Step 4: Reduced-motion fallback**
  `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` → freeze all orbit/drift/reveal animations to static; mesh-bg renders as a still gradient.

- [ ] **Step 5: Render-verify**
  Save, rasterize the loaded page + one demo expanded to PNG, Read both. Confirm: mesh atmosphere reads, `NETY` is the hero object, glass cards legible, no layout breakage.

- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**
  ```bash
  git add apps/nety.html && git commit -m "feat(nety): Kinetic Mesh shell — mesh bg, giant hero, glass node-cards"
  ```

