### Task 3: Access section — passport, registration, share-earn, invites, recovery mock

Implements spec §3.1–§3.3, §3.7. The bridge's visible start.

**Files:**
- Modify: `apps/nety.html` (new `<section id="access">` after the demos)

**Interfaces:**
- Consumes: `window.nety` (Task 2), `.glass`/`.passport` styles (Task 1).
- Produces: `#access` anchor; a `[data-stars]` chip the Verify/Stars sections reuse.

- [ ] **Step 0: Onboarding "first steps" strip** — CSS-pure, always-visible, right under the hero (per spec §3 / page order §8). A numbered strip walking the full on-ramp: 1·what nety is → 2·run/contribute (open) → 3·your `profily-mini` appears → 4·get an invite **or** verify yourself → 5·register into `appy` (play & store). Each step links to its section (`#access`, etc.); checkbox-dismissible; completed steps dim via `:has()`. Zero JS.
- [ ] **Step 1: Passport = `profily-mini`** — glowing card showing **@handle / mock peerId**, your **hardware contribution** (resources shared → Global), **live presence** badge (LIVE/RECENT/REACHABLE/DARK), and your **stage** (`newbie`→`legend`) badge, plus the live star/progress chip. Label it **`profily-mini`** (open, from running nety); note "full **`profily`** → in appy". This is the seed of the full profily.
- [ ] **Step 2: Registration form + entry paths** — frame it as **crossing `mini`(`nety`, open) → `basic`(`appy`)**, showing the **four paths in** (§3.1 A–D): **A** invite code · **B** authenticate yourself (Telegram/email/phone/biometrics tabs) · **C** earn points (share hardware / approved content) · **D** curator admission (+ further auth). Fields invite-code OR auth panel, @handle, display-name, "generate keypair"; on submit call `nety.register`, echo live outputs (validated handle, peerId, signed invite link); empty/invalid invite + no auth → blocked state. (The script's one job.)
- [ ] **Step 3: Share-resources → earn** — reuse the existing demo-3 role+meter pattern; "share" calls `nety.addStars(...)`; note higher stages unlock further resources + donation directing (§5.2).
- [ ] **Step 3b: Publishing & moderation queue** — publish options (static page / post / file) gated behind ≥Telegram; published items render in a CSS-pure **pending → curator review → live** queue state; **approved → live credits points** (`nety.addStars`), pending/rejected give nothing. Note volunteer curators (§3.8) review it; real mechanism deferred.
- [ ] **Step 4: Invites** — CSS `:has()` reveal of a signed invite token; show single-use vs multi-use (multi-use shows "validate each registrant" + 72h pending note); revoke/disown controls (visual).
- [ ] **Step 5: Recovery mock** — self-backup prompt + social-quorum visual + "rotated · in probation" badge (§3.7); illustrative only.
- [ ] **Step 6: Render-verify** — rasterize blank form, filled+submitted (outputs shown), invites revealed; Read all. Confirm live outputs echo typed input.
- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**
  ```bash
  git add apps/nety.html && git commit -m "feat(nety): Access — passport, registration, share-earn, invites, recovery mock"
  ```

